      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, it is absolutely possible to achieve dangerous levels of Vitamin D toxicity relatively quickly with such high doses. Consuming 50,000 IU daily for two weeks can increase your blood levels significantly, creating a risk of hypercalcemia, which puts serious strain on your kidneys. Even if you stop after two weeks, the damage or symptoms can develop, making it a risk not worth taking for a temporary boost. Please consult a healthcare provider before starting any high-dose regimen.",
      "source": "target",
